## **5. Library and Book**
```python
# Library → Book? (Library has books)
# Book → Library? (Book knows which library it belongs to)
```

## **6. Teacher and Classroom**
```python
# Teacher → Classroom? (Teacher teaches in classroom)
# Classroom → Teacher? (Classroom has assigned teacher)
```

## **7. Restaurant and Menu**
```python
# Restaurant → Menu? (Restaurant offers menu)
# Menu → Restaurant? (Menu belongs to restaurant)
```

## **8. Bank and Account**
```python
# Bank → Account? (Bank manages accounts)
# Account → Bank? (Account knows its bank)
# Account → Customer? (Account belongs to customer)
# Customer → Account? (Customer owns accounts)
```

## **9. Airline and Flight**
```python
# Airline → Flight? (Airline operates flights)
# Flight → Airline? (Flight is operated by airline)
# Flight → Passenger? (Flight has passengers)
# Passenger → Flight? (Passenger books flights)
```

## **10. Hospital and Patient**
```python
# Hospital → Patient? (Hospital treats patients)
# Patient → Hospital? (Patient is treated at hospital)
# Doctor → Patient? (Doctor treats patients)
# Patient → Doctor? (Patient has assigned doctor)
```

## **11. E-commerce Order System**
```python
# Customer → Order? (Customer places orders)
# Order → Customer? (Order belongs to customer)
# Order → Product? (Order contains products)
# Product → Order? (Product appears in orders)
```

## **12. Social Media Post**
```python
# User → Post? (User creates posts)
# Post → User? (Post knows its author)
# Post → Comment? (Post has comments)
# Comment → Post? (Comment belongs to post)
# Comment → User? (Comment made by user)
```

## **13. University Course System**
```python
# Course → Student? (Course has enrolled students)
# Student → Course? (Student takes courses)
# Course → Professor? (Course taught by professor)
# Professor → Course? (Professor teaches courses)
```

## **14. Smart Home System**
```python
# User → Device? (User controls devices)
# Device → User? (Device has owner)
# Hub → Device? (Hub manages devices)
# Device → Hub? (Device connects to hub)
```

**Instructions for all exercises:** For each pair, write minimal Python class skeletons showing only the attribute references (arrows) that would implement the relationships described.